How to avoid creating duplicates from bank feeds: 

1ï¸âƒ£ When booking credit card payments do the following:  

âž¡ï¸Check both the credit card and the checking account bank feeds to ensure date/amount tie then book from only ONE of them credit card payment: both transactions should leave bank feeds together: check it! 

âž¡ï¸If the credit card payment option isn't clear, book the bank payment first, categorize it to the credit card account, THEN go to the credit card bank feed and MATCH the payment to the transaction you just created.

2ï¸âƒ£ If you code things (like checks you printed) in your books, make sure to match the check in your bank feeds to that transaction or you will have duplicates of that check.

3ï¸âƒ£ Just because a transaction in bank feeds matches a transaction in your books doesn't mean it is a match:  check dates, check numbers, vendors/customers, etc with the bank description.
